            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science missions contributed $22,539,274 in direct obligations to NJ-07 businesses between FY2023 and FY2025\n* Messer LLC (Bridgewater/Stewartsville) is a major industrial partner with over $28.5 million in cumulative NASA contract awards\n* Hamamatsu Corp (Bridgewater) provides essential high-tech components for NASA scientific instrumentation\n* Sustained SMD funding protects local high-skill jobs and reinforces New Jersey's role in the national aerospace supply chain",
            "rationale": "Utilizes specific local spending data for NJ-07, citing Messer LLC and Hamamatsu Corp along with the $22.5M obligation figure.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:rd8212e9a669e4555bc0a339a58b0a4cd:7213e89fb2e2",
            "label": "Background Information or Other Comments",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Space science is a critical front in the technological competition with China, which is rapidly expanding lunar and planetary capabilities\n* NASA investments yield an estimated 3:1 economic return by driving industrial innovation and STEM workforce demand\n* Funding restoration is essential to prevent further loss of highly specialized civil servant and contractor expertise following FY26 disruptions\n* Maintaining US leadership in space science ensures the nation sets the international norms for 21st-century exploration",
            "rationale": "Draws on strategic talking points regarding competition with China, economic ROI, and workforce stability to provide a compelling background narrative.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
